Pre-Game Insights: Australia have a 'good reference' of how to win knockout matches and have won the 2015 ODI World Cup and the T20 World Cup in 2021.
South Africa will continue with their'must-win' mindset when facing Australia in the semifinal.
South Africa's chasing troubles in the tournament have been well documented, losing against India and Netherlands while chasing.
Temba Bavuma may miss the semifinal due to a hamstring injury.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rassie Van der Dussen scored an unbeaten 76 off 95 to chase down Afghanistan's 244 and take South Africa to a five-wicket win.
South Africa's win-loss ratio looks pretty good in their favor when batting first and 50-50 when chasing.
Reeza Hendricks is most likely to open the batting if Temba Bavuma misses the semifinal.
